#### Analyzer package

Example: [Microsoft.CodeAnalysis.BannedApiAnalyzers](https://www.nuget.org/packages/Microsoft.CodeAnalysis.BannedApiAnalyzers)

#### Package Version

Example: v2.9.4 (Latest)

#### Diagnostic ID
RS0030

#### Repro steps

BannedSymbols.txt: 
```
T:N.B
```
.cs:
```csharp
namespace N
{
    public class B { }

    public class C
    {
        B B => new B();
    }

    public interface I
    {
        B GetB(B otherB);
    }
}
```

#### Expected behavior

All four occurrences of `B` should be reported.

#### Actual behavior

Only `C.B`'s symbol in expression body is reported (in `new B();`)

